name: Nothing Really Mattress : archival print
description: Photographic print on museum quality archival paper (Hahnemuhle Photo rag). Images are scanned from black and white film. Available in the following sizes 8x10 open edition: $50 11×17 open edition: $99 16x20 limited edition of 25 $250 All prints are created using archival pigment inks on 100% cotton rag paper with a luster finish. The quoted dimensions are for the size of paper containing the images, not the printed image itself. We do not crop the originals. All prints have a minimum border of .5 inches to allow for framing. From the photo series Austin Seen, in progress... Photographed and printed in Austin, TX

name: Inscribed/signed copy of Proud to Serve: Portraits of LGBT Veterans photography book
description: Proud to Serve: Portraits of Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual and Transgender Veterans is an 88 page full color publication featuring 65 portraits and stories of LGBT Veterans who served their country in silence or were discharged under the “Don’t Ask, Don’t Tell” law. On August 25, 2010, Jo Ann began a twenty-eight day road trip around the United States, driving 10,167 miles, 31 states from New York to California and back to photograph and record the stories of 46 of the 65 the LGBT Veterans featured in this project. Included in the book are a selection of iPhone images of America taken during Jo Ann's twenty-eight day road trip. Be sure to note any specific name you would like inscribed to. a glimpse inside Proud to Serve [video]
